The paper deals with the design and analysis of adaptive beamforming algorithms, which are commonly used in signal processing applications. The paper focuses on the joint iterative optimization of filters, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SP), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic gradient and recursive least-squares adaptive algorithms, which are techniques that are commonly used in neural networks and other machine learning applications. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
